Pre-Game Insights: Harambee Stars take on the Indomitable Lions on match day three of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) qualifiers at the Stade Omnisport Ahmadou Ahidjo in Yaoundé.
Kenya is searching for a win to move back to the top of Group J after Zimbabwe's victory over Namibia.
Kenya's head coach Engin Firat expects a tough match but is hopeful for a good result.
Firat emphasized the importance of planning for both the match in Yaoundé and the return match in Kampala.
Firat has been boosted by the availability of striker Michael Olunga and defender Daniel Anyembe.
Centreback Joseph Okumu is back fully fit after an injury.
Cameroon has a potent squad with notable players like goalkeeper Andre Onana, Bryan Mbeumo, and Carlos Baleba.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cameroon will have full support at home, creating a potentially hostile environment for Kenya.
Kenya is unbeaten in seven matches in a row.
